Sentencas: A common approach to reliable load-following is to slave fuel cell response to the reactants supply subsystem (e.g. fuel processor).
Titulo: Simulating process settings for unslaved SOFC response to increases in load demand

Sentencas: A change-in-power demand may be time-sensitive, however, and slaving the fuel cell response to that of the slower balance-of-plant components may not be practical.
Titulo: Simulating process settings for unslaved SOFC response to increases in load demand

Sentencas: A model has been constructed to simulate the unrestrained load-following characteristics of a commercial-grade fuel cell.
Titulo: Simulating process settings for unslaved SOFC response to increases in load demand

Sentencas: Analyses have shown that initial conditions exist which facilitate timely responses to increases in load demand, among them lower fuel utilization, larger operating voltage and optimized cell potential reduction.
Titulo: Simulating process settings for unslaved SOFC response to increases in load demand
